Horizon as boundary: surface fields fixed. Energy and angular momentum 



In order to avoid unnecessary cluttering of the equations, we shall take
the black hole horizon at  as the dynamical one and the cosmological horizon at
 as the boundary. After the analysis is carried out it will be indicated
how the conclusions are changed if the role of the horizons is reversed. Those changes
will be simple but significant.

